    Scope and Contents
Frost recalls coal mining work in Alabama and Springfield, Illinois: mining jobs, company houses, stores, scrip pay and wages; mechanization, safety, and equipment; unions and the mine wars; ethnicity and the Depression. 3 tapes, 270 mins. 
Interview by Barbara Herndon, 1976 
